5000|$|On 7 December 1929 in the Bay of Biscay Arlanza and a German ship went to {{help the}} [...] Italian cargo ship , which was sinking. Arlanza rescued all of the crew except three, who were rescued by the German ship. the Italian Government, Lloyd's of London and RMSP awarded medals and made presentations {{to a number of}} Arlanzas crew for the bravery and {{outstanding}} seamanship they showed in the rescue. Able Seaman William Bonas, for example, received a bronze Lloyd's Medal for Saving Life at Sea and a bronze Medaglia al <b>valore</b> <b>di</b> Marina.|$|E
